	<Title>
		Weight loss: Unhook yourself from food
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Do thoughts and feelings about food stand in your way of learning healthy-eating habits? Try these five steps: 1. Know your habits. For a few weeks, jot down what, when and why you eat. See if any patterns emerge. 2. Change gradually. When you&apos;ve identified problem behaviors, make specific plans to change the behaviors. 3. Don&apos;t dwell on what you&apos;re giving up. Enjoy an occasional treat and get plenty of variety to help curb cravings. 4. Don&apos;t give up on yourself. An occasional setback is to be expected. Get right back on the bandwagon.&lt;/p&gt;
